Members: Song and Rue (and your pets)
Icee | Rue | ⚡ 07-Aug-22 12:22 PM
In the day or night time, the daycare is always open to you till the clock strikes ten. In the Botanical gardens, a humble little booth of wood stands out in the front where two figures manage it from behind. A short game is being hosted there, several placards of animals drawn onto them. Why not take a chance while you're here? It wouldn't hurt! The back section of the gardens have been fenced off into sections for the festival, where large play areas for animals have been made. Makeshift toys from spare sheets, wooden sticks, and other materials are shaped a little crudely into animal shapes scatter around the grass. One area houses a pond, made similar in shape to a rock garden where the more aquatic animals can happily splash about. For those worried about their more air friendly pets, there's iced walls, and a thin ice roof blocking them from flying too far in another section. The pets are allowed to wander about as they please, and their owners can pick them up when their relaxation day is done! Benches in the garden remained untouched, still allowing for those who want to relax there in leisure to do so. It might be a little noisier than usual with the cries of the many pets that have now taken over the gardens.
12:24
Game Description
During this game you will be given a silhouette for your Character to decipher. Once posted, you will then roll a <!skill (Lore)> for your character. From there. Either myself or Eve will slide into your DMs to relay if you character has correctly deciphered the creature or if the silhouette happened to be a bit too confusing for them.
If they guess correctly, it’s onto the next round! If they guess incorrectly, well… sorry buds— it’s Game Over!
Your character is allowed to comeback and retry this game every 2 ooc Days (subject to change if quasi is in a failing mood) should they not reach their desired Prize tier on the first go around.
There is a total of 5 rounds. Each round progressively getting more and more difficult over time. If you manage to make it through all 5 rounds however…You will be given the chance to enter into the Grand Prize Battle Royale! This will take place sometime within the last week of the Summer or Adora-tion Event.
So there will be plenty of time to try and snag a spot!
 (edited)
12:25
Game Rules
As stated above there will be a total of 5 rounds. Usage of the <!skill (Lore)> will be used.
Round 1 and 2 will require at Minimum 1 success on your roll. (If first roll on round 1 is failed. We will allow one reroll.)
Round 3 and 4 will require at Minimum 2 successes on your roll.
And finally, round 5, the challenge round. For this round you will require a Minimum of 3 successes on your roll. For those big-brained fellow of Lore 6-8 you must roll a success of 4.
Groups of 4-5 will be able to play at one time.
For those with low and or no lore at all, We have decided to implement the Phone a friend clause! With this option your character can bring a partner with higher lore to play in their stead. However, it will only be the original character that receives the prize. The friend will not. But fear not friend! For they are free to play on the next available round if they have not already played for themselves within the set time limit!
Also we would like to mention, due to Quasis unfavorable mood swings at times- these rolling can be subject to change should quasi decides no one is allow to win. But if that time comes we will be sure to inform! Until then- ENJOY- HAVE FUN- AND GOOD LUCK GUESSING!
UPDATE: NOW EACH PLAYER WILL BE GRANTED TWO REROLLS (edited)

22:51
Rules for the Finale! The game rules will change to give everyone a fair chance, whether or not your lore stat is 0 or 8! Instead of rolling lore or borrowing lore, you will be rolling a dice of 1d100. There will be 5 rounds, if there is a tie after the 5 rounds, we will enter sudden death rounds. To get past the rounds, you need at least a 75 or over to pass. The ones who have the most successes during the rounds will be noted and placed into the final 3 rounds. - You will have two rerolls during each round for the first 5 rounds! During the sudden death rounds, remaining participants will roll like usual, but without rerolls. You simply roll to see who gets the 75, and they move on! If no one gets a 75 on that one roll, they will reroll for another round. The contestants that hit 75 goes to the next round. If no one else gets a 75, the winner is set! (Please wait for everyone to either finish their rolls/rerolls before going so we can keep track!) Your base lore stat is a bonus that you will add to your D100 roll. We also want people with their lore to get a little advantage for being brainy! ✨ Example: (Your roll of !1d100) and your lore stat is 3 then you simply add it to your roll 72 + 3 = 75! Success! You have passed the round. (edited)
